<body>
  <h1>Privacy Policy for OneTap Journal</h1>

  <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
  <p>One-Tap Journal is an offline, single-user diary application. It is published by <strong>World Crafter Studios</strong>.</p>

  <h2>2. What data we collect</h2>
  <p>We store the text you type into the app on your device. If you enable a passcode, we store it securely as a salted hash. No other personal data is collected.</p>

  <h2>3. How we use the data</h2>
  <p>Your entries are used only within the app. If you export data, the app creates an encrypted file. We never send your data to any server.</p>

  <h2>4. How we protect the data</h2>
  <p>Journal entries are stored using 256-bit AES encryption. Passcodes are hashed securely. All data stays on your device unless you manually export it.</p>

  <h2>5. Data sharing</h2>
  <p>We do not share, sell, or upload your data to anyone.</p>

  <h2>6. Your choices</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Set/change/remove passcode via Settings → Require Passcode</li>
    <li>Delete entries manually or uninstall the app to delete all data</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>7. Children’s privacy</h2>
  <p>This app is not intended for children under 13. No data is knowingly collected from them.</p>

  <h2>8. Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>We may update this policy. The current version is always available at this address.</p>

  <h2>9. Contact</h2>
  <p>For questions, email: <strong>WorldCrafterStudios@gmail.com</strong></p>
</body>
</html>
